Implemented a generalized parser fix for U.S.C. section matching and added a regression test for this packet’s two sample IDs.

- Updated section-reference matching to treat Unicode dash variants as equivalent to ASCII `-`, and to allow flexible dash matching in section tokens. This now applies to citation token parsing and all section-reference lookups (direct, starts-with, embedded heading, coarse heading): [legal_modal_parser.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-vector-8h-20260518T072401Z-codex-compiler_parser/worktrees/agent-codex-compiler_parser-packet-000040-20260518_121749/ipfs_datasets_py/optimizers/logic_theorem_optimizer/legal_modal_parser.py:57), [legal_modal_parser.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-vector-8h-20260518T072401Z-codex-compiler_parser/worktrees/agent-codex-compiler_parser-packet-000040-20260518_121749/ipfs_datasets_py/optimizers/logic_theorem_optimizer/legal_modal_parser.py:501).
- Added packet replay fixture/test for `us-code-16-773b-d418534f697a23b1` and `us-code-16-460vv-17-9b754fd1c1a1e8a7`, asserting deterministic codification/transferred fallback in both `regex` and `spacy` compiler backends: [test_modal_codec.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-vector-8h-20260518T072401Z-codex-compiler_parser/worktrees/agent-codex-compiler_parser-packet-000040-20260518_121749/tests/unit_tests/logic/modal/test_modal_codec.py:395), [test_modal_codec.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-vector-8h-20260518T072401Z-codex-compiler_parser/worktrees/agent-codex-compiler_parser-packet-000040-20260518_121749/tests/unit_tests/logic/modal/test_modal_codec.py:1331).

Tests run:

- `pytest -q tests/unit_tests/logic/modal/test_modal_codec.py -k "16_773b_and_16_460vv_17"` passed.
- `pytest -q tests/unit/optimizers/logic_theorem_optimizer/test_legal_modal_parser.py -k "sec_prefixed_transferred_headings_for_known_uscode_samples or sec_prefixed_heading_zero_formula_sample_for_15_1693l"` passed.
